⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Beethoven's Ninth
node ACO · ACO · ⟦Beethoven's Ninth:ACO:a20771⟧

WHO   — Beethoven's Ninth — the beauty conditioned to nausea
WHAT  — The cruel side-effect that proves the cure's blunt brutality: in killing Alex's capacity for evil, it kills his capacity for transcendence.
WHERE — ACO · A CLOCKWORK ORANGE  Framework inputs: A Clockwork Orange (Anthony Burgess, 1962)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the warning shows that you cannot surgically remove the bad without maiming the good — the soul is not so divisible.
HOW   — By being the soundtrack to the conditioning, until the Ninth induces the same agony as the violence.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I was the one beautiful thing in a brutal boy — and the cure that took his cruelty took me with it, because you cannot cut out the dark without bleeding the light.

